#begin
point
point num x y z

num can either be 0 or 1
Example :
point 0 220 320 100
#end

#begin
radius
radius num rad
radius rad

If num is specified then s and t radius for that point is set to rad.
If num is not specified then s and t radius for both the points is set to rad.
#end

#begin
normalize
Point coordinates are normalize i.e. coordinates are truncated.
#end

#begin
rads
rads num rad
rads rad

Specify the size for red handle

If num is specified then s (red-axis) radius for that point is set to rad.
If num is not specified then s radius for both the points is set to rad.

#end

#begin
radt
radt num rad
radt rad

Specify the size for green handle

If num is specified then t (green-axis) radius for that point is set to rad.
If num is not specified then t radius for both the points is set to rad.

#end

#begin
angle
angle degrees
Set angle of rotation about blue axis.
#end

#begin
save
Save two end points to a text file.
#end


#begin
moves
moves [-]

Move the widget in the direction of S-axis (red).

"moves -" will move the widget in the opposite direction of S-axis (red).
#end

#begin
movet
movet [-]

Move the widget in the direction of T-axis (green).

"movet -" will move the widget in the opposite direction of T-axis (green).
#end

#begin
keyboard
Start Keyboard help
#end

#begin
x
Red handle selected.
#end

#begin
y
Green handle selected.
#end

#begin
z
Blue handle selected.
#end

#begin
f
Flip endpoints.
#end

#begin
v
Hide widget.
#end

#begin
DEL
Delete the widget
#end

#begin
Up/Down
Move widget in the currently selected handle direction.
#end

#begin
Shift + Up/Down
Move in larger steps.
#end

#begin
Left/Right
Rotate widget about the currently selected handle.
#end

#begin
Shift + Left/Right
Rotate with larger angles.
#end

#begin
Mouse right/middle button drag
Translate whole widget or either point depending upon where the drag started.
#end

#begin
Mouse Ctrl + right/middle button drag
Change the size of the widget.
#end

#begin
Mouse left drag
Rotate widget about selected axis.
#end